race.comment: KAYLEEN'S PROFIT (7) has been slow out of the machine then worked home evenly without threatening in her two runs this time in work, both over shorter trips. Ready for this longer journey now. The addition of blinkers may switch her on early which helps the cause. Clear top pick especially with the stablemate being scratched. KALKANLI (1) is nearing a win, the latest offering a close second here at this trip at Class 1 level. Only needs to hold that form to be right in the finish. BIANCO NERO (6) is dour so getting beyond nine furlongs for the first time looks a good move. TORTILLA (3) produced the best run of his latest campaign last start at Dalby, getting out to ten furlongs. Respect.
